Step 1: Install Virtualization Software
Oracle VirtualBox

Step 2: Download Cloudera QuickStart VM
 https://downloads.cloudera.com/demo_vm/virtualbox/cloudera-quickstart-vm-5.13.0-0-virtualbox.zip

Step 3: Import the VM into VirtualBox

Step 4: Start Cloudera VM

Step 5: Start Hadoop Services
Open terminal and run:
sudo service hadoop-hdfs-namenode start
sudo service hadoop-hdfs-datanode start
sudo service hadoop-yarn-resourcemanager start
sudo service hadoop-yarn-nodemanager start

Step 6: Verify Hadoop
Check HDFS:
hdfs dfsadmin -report

Step 7: Create HDFS Directory
hdfs dfs -mkdir /input

Step 8: Upload File to HDFS
hdfs dfs -put sample.txt /input

Step 9: Verify Upload
Run this command to list files inside the HDFS input directory:
hdfs dfs -ls /input
